Add the right reference here.  Don't disable the shellcheck warning.

Example:
```
meta-bletchley/recipes-bletchley/plat-svc/files/bletchley-early-sys-init:# shellcheck source=meta-facebook/meta-bletchley/recipes-bletchley/plat-tools/files/bletchley-common-functions
```
Can we get a comment as to what this file is for?  systemd format allows comments.
I will add another multi gpiod commit after I modify dts line name.
It is for gpio initial and set power status.
Do these actually need an EXPORT?
I will add ad new commit for gpio monitor after I modify DTS line name.
Are we going to get a real driver for this device?

Do you mean we need to add an attribute to control it?

So far ltc4287 driver doesn't support it.
https://lore.kernel.org/all/20231123015440.199822-3-Delphine_CC_Chiu@Wiwynn.com/
Control what?  I have no idea what this is doing.  To me it is a bunch of random bytes.
I misunderstood it. I have fixed it.
What is this??  We may not store state in random /tmp files.

We can't obtain the power good status when the GPIO monitor starts, and the Power State Manager (PSM) doesn't synchronize the power good status from GPIO. Therefore, we need a power good cache to check it.
We should go back to some source of truth.  Either systemd service state, GPIO, phosphor-state-manager enum value.  Writing files in /tmp isn't acceptable.
Change i2c command to get power good
Why is this called "rev" if it is a power state?

We need to get a driver written for the CPLD or get it to emulate a GPIO properly.  We should not permanently have `i2cget` calls embedded in shell scripts.

This doesn't have to be done immediately, but we should discuss offline what the plan is here.
You're going to have issue with this echo conflicting with the echo on line 40 and 44.
Do we need to return at this point?  Why aren't we using return rather than echo?

Fix title.

"meta-facebook: harma: power control support"
Not sure why I was reviewing PS9 earlier today.  Looks good now.  Thanks.
